THE Bushiris have lost their R5,5 million home after failing to present themselves in the Pretoria Magistrates Court, as per the court’s instruction. This after they fled the country, defying their bail conditions. Magistrate Thandi Theledi made the order to seize their estate in Centurion, Tshwane this morning. The controversial self-proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, Mary, spend the night at the Malawian prison, while filing for bail. They handed themselves over to the Malawi authorities on Tuesday. This was after an Interpol was sent to their country by the South African government. The couple have fled to their home country allegedly last Wednesday, stating that they didn’t feel safe in Mzansi. Two warrant of arrests have been issued for the couple. They are facing charges of theft, fraud and money laundering.